## Transcript

This lesson addresses the feedback moments most managers dread — delivering constructive feedback about serious issues with care and directness. Jordan and Sam explore how to prepare for difficult conversations, manage your own emotions beforehand, and stay focused on behavior and impact rather than character.

They discuss strategies for staying calm when the conversation gets heated, how to hold the line on important feedback without being harsh, and the importance of separating the person from the problem. The hosts also talk about when to escalate, when to pause, and how to follow up after a tough conversation to maintain the relationship.

